@startuml Amdox-ERP-Sequence
title Amdox ERP — Sequence Diagram (Login + Demand Forecast)

skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
actor User
participant "React\nFrontend" as FE
participant "NestJS API\nGateway :5000" as API
participant "Auth\nMiddleware" as MW
participant "Service\nLayer" as SVC
database "PostgreSQL 17\n(Prisma)" as DB
participant "ML Service\nFastAPI :8000" as ML
queue "Redis\n(BullMQ)" as RQ

== Authentication ==
User -> FE : enter email + password
FE -> API : POST /auth/login
API -> SVC : authService.login()
SVC -> DB : SELECT user + roles + permissions
DB --> SVC : user record
SVC -> SVC : bcrypt.compare(password)
SVC -> DB : INSERT session, audit_log
SVC --> API : { accessToken, refreshToken }
API --> FE : 200 + JWT
FE -> FE : store token (Zustand)

== Authenticated Request ==
User -> FE : open Forecast page
FE -> API : GET /supply/forecasts\n(Bearer token)
API -> MW : verify JWT + RBAC
MW --> API : req.user set
API -> SVC : forecastingService.generate()
SVC -> DB : SELECT sales history
DB --> SVC : stock movements
SVC -> ML : POST /forecast/predict\n{ historical_data }
ML -> ML : LSTM / Prophet predict
ML --> SVC : { predicted_qty, mape }
SVC -> DB : INSERT forecast
SVC --> API : forecast result
API --> FE : 200 + chart data
FE --> User : render forecast 📈

== Async Job (background) ==
SVC -> RQ : enqueue retrain job
RQ -> ML : nightly retrain
ML --> RQ : model saved
@enduml
